verbose_text: Other studies such as that by Llorente-Cortes et al. showed an increase of cyclooxygenase 2 (COX-2) and LDL-C receptor related protein, representing a decrease in the expression of monocyte chemoattractant protein 1 (MCP-1) in 49 asymptomatic individuals with high CVD risk after a 3-month intervention with the MedDiet [XREF_BIBR].
